37
00:02:11,085 --> 00:02:13,586
you know, members of the public had had raised some concerns.

38
00:02:13,666 --> 00:02:19,487
Councilors had raised some concerns about the regulation of trees on private way and private property.

39
00:02:20,628 --> 00:02:31,551
And at the conclusion of that meeting, the city council moved to request that the city solicitor and our legal council take the proposed language of the tree preservation protection and replacement ordinance.

40
00:02:32,091 --> 00:02:46,725
and properly place the proposed changes within Medford's existing city ordinances that included changes to existing ordinance language regarding public shade trees that fall under chapter 87, creating a proposed general zoning ordinance for the protection of certain trees on private property.

41
00:02:47,705 --> 00:02:55,707
separating section six into a tree committee ordinance, a separate tree committee ordinance that would be placed in chapter two, article three of Benford's ordinances.

42
00:02:56,468 --> 00:03:08,071
And that would also include any other suggestions or proposed amendments that legal counsel deemed necessary while preserving the intent of the proposed language discussed at the council at our June meeting.

43
00:03:09,291 --> 00:03:13,773
My understanding is that we received a communication

44
00:03:16,175 --> 00:03:27,746
