I know that it was a long motion that KP law got, and I could try to simplify the language, but basically what we asked was for the existing ordinance, which has all of these different pieces put together into a single ordinance for it to be split up into an amendment modifying the city ordinance around public shade trees.

125
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:13,143
taking anything that refers to private property and putting that in its own bucket.

126
00:11:13,684 --> 00:11:22,067
And then also taking the proposed tree committee and having that be kind of a separate piece since that would be fall under a different chapter of the existing city ordinance.

127
00:11:22,607 --> 00:11:36,512
So really what we had requested was just that that framework be laid out, that we take this single ordinance and split it up into three constituent pieces so that we can have a discussion on them and so that those items could

128
00:11:37,492 --> 00:11:43,276
you know, be adopted and or amended relative to the current structure of the city ordinances.

129
00:11:44,957 --> 00:11:50,862
So, you know, that to me, that whole motion is not really a policy question.

130
