142
00:13:05,016 --> 00:13:13,880
It sounds like you may, there may be a version that's after this, but I did, I believe provide comments in the same draft that this time, but comments on as well.

143
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,221
And I think one of the

144
00:13:17,232 --> 00:13:18,713
topics that you just brought up is really important.

145
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:20,254
The public versus private.

146
00:13:20,894 --> 00:13:27,838
I mean, I read this and I see where it talks about what the city's responsibilities would be on private trees.

147
00:13:28,398 --> 00:13:36,942
But a lot of that seems to me, in my personal opinion, in direct conflict with existing mass general law when it comes to private trees and how they're protected.

148
00:13:37,603 --> 00:13:41,645
So I think those have to be sussed out and I think that's maybe what KP Law is kind of pointing out there.

149
00:13:42,283 --> 00:13:42,723
potentially.

150
00:13:43,063 --> 00:13:55,910
So I think that has to be sussed out and organized before myself and I think Aggie would agree with me to make substantial comments on the meat of the public tree portion.

151
00:13:56,570 --> 00:14:02,093
Because as I think everybody knows, the tree warden is in care and control of the public shade trees here in the city of Medford.

152
00:14:03,133 --> 00:14:03,693
So there's that.

153
00:14:03,713 --> 00:14:06,134
So I think sussing that piece out is critical.

154
00:14:07,095 --> 00:14:11,357
And then the other kind of big

155
00:14:11,924 --> 00:14:27,938
big overarching comment I think I have is, you know, something like this is obviously adds sort of layers to existing administrative processes and also adds new administrative processes in both the DPW and the building department code enforcement.

156
00:14:27,958 --> 00:14:38,087
So with an ordinance like this, I would want to see personally some sort of analysis of required FTEs, how that grows over time, and then what

157
00:14:39,548 --> 00:14:51,017
kind of operating budgets we're talking about for this type of human resource, because I think it's mostly a sort of a staff time thing, an administrative procedure type of thing.

158
00:14:51,758 --> 00:14:55,821
Anyway, so I think those are the two big issues for me that need to get sussed out.

159
00:14:57,875 --> 00:14:59,916
